| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2001-05-17]]
| accessdate = 2008-09-15}}</ref> The following season, [[2001-02 in English football|2001&ndash;02]], he made 28 appearances in the [[Football League First Division|First Division]]. Birmingham reached the [[Football League Championship Play-Offs#2002|play-offs]] again for the fourth consecutive season, this time gaining promotiton after beating [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]] in the semi-final and [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] in the final. This time, Woodhouse did not play in any of the matches.<ref name="Dublin dents Birmingham">{{cite news
| title = Dublin dents Birmingham
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_1/1951115.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2002-04-28]]
| accessdate = 2008-09-15}}</ref><ref name="Birmingham snatch dramatic win">{{cite news
| title = Birmingham snatch dramatic win
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_1/1962328.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2002-05-02]]
| accessdate = 2008-09-15}}</ref><ref name="Birmingham reach Premiership">{{cite news
| title = Birmingham reach Premiership
| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/eng_div_1/1979806.stm
| publisher = BBC Sport
| date = [[2002-05-12]]
| accessdate = 2008-09-15}}</ref> He made just three appearances for Birmingham City in the [[Premier League]],<ref name="soccerbase" /> before being loaned out to [[Rotherham United F.C.|Rotherham United]] in January 2003. [[Grimsby Town F.C.|Grimsby Town]] and [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] were also reportedly interested in signing the midfielder.<ref name="Woodhouse in demand">{{cite news
